definitions.definition: Of or pertaining to the pharynx .

Articulated with the pharynx ; a term usually describing a consonant which is articulated by the rear area of the tongue being raised to below the region between the uvula and the pharyngeal wall. The term cannot apply to a plosive or stop consonant.
